arts.ttl: Huff and puff not enough as early goal sinks Stevenage at Orient
arts.sum: Brandon Hanlan couldn't get onto the end of a Charlie Goode flick on as Boro forced a series of corners but even though it was better, it still felt like they were knocking on the door without taking their hands out of their pockets. And so it proved, Orient taking the 1-0 win to bolster their League One play-off push, while Boro still sit firmly in mid-table.

arts.ttl: Charlie Kelman gives Leyton Orient victory against Stevenage
arts.sum: Kelman struck his 19th goal of the campaign to move the hosts up to eighth in Sky Bet League One.

arts.ttl: US-based consortium close to ambitious £18m takeover of Leyton Orient
arts.sum: Plans could lead to potential American football franchise Buying group understood to be led by David Gandler A US-based consortium is closing in on an £18m majority takeover of Leyton Orient as part of a plan that could lead to an American football franchise being established in east London. The League One club announced last month that they had entered exclusive negotiations with a potential buyer which are believed to be at an advanced stage. Continue reading...

arts.ttl: Stevenage chairman gives full backing to manager Alex Revell
arts.sum: "We had several people we talked to beforehand and every time I ever spoke to somebody in an informal interview, I just kept coming away thinking they were no better than Revs. A fans' forum at the Lamex say the question raised, what has Phil Wallace thought about the League One season so far, and what does he think of the 'Revs out' murmurings.
